<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?>
<xsl:stylesheet version="1.1"
	xmlns:xsl="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Transform" xmlns:fo="http://www.w3.org/1999/XSL/Format"
	exclude-result-prefixes="fo" xmlns:fn="http://www.w3.org/2005/02/xpath-functions"
	xmlns:java="java">

	<xsl:template match="/" name="LPL-AMEND-MD">

		<fo:block>
			<xsl:call-template name="CommonHeader" />
		</fo:block>

		<fo:block text-align="center" margin-left="1.3in"
			margin-right="1.3in" font-size="12px"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			space-before="5mm" space-after="5mm" font-weight="bold">
			MARYLAND AMENDATORY ENDORSEMENT
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">

			<fo:block space-after="4mm">
				In consideration of the premium charged, it is agreed that Section VI.,
				General Condition D., Cancellation and Nonrenewal, is deleted and
				replaced with the following:
			</fo:block>
			
			<fo:block space-after="4mm">


				<fo:list-block>
					<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
						<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								<fo:inline font-weight="bold">D.</fo:inline>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-label>
						<fo:list-item-body start-indent="7mm">
							<fo:block space-after="4mm" font-weight="bold">
								Cancellation, Nonrenewal, Premium Increase and Conditional Renewal
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
							<fo:list-block>
							<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block font-weight="bold">
								1.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
							<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
								Cancellation
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
							<fo:list-block>
							<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(a)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
							<fo:block>
								The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> may cancel this policy at any time prior to the
								expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline> by providing prior written notice
								to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or by surrender of this policy to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or its
								authorized agent. If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
								shall return 90% of the unearned portion of the premium.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(b)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may only cancel this policy for nonpayment of premium.
								This policy may be canceled by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named
								Insured</fo:inline>, at the address shown in Item 1. of the Declarations, written
								notice of cancellation at least 10 days before the effective date of
								cancellation. Such notice shall state the state the reason for
								cancellation and the effective date of cancellation stated in such
								notice shall become the expiration date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>. Such
								notice shall be sent by a first-class mail tracking method or by
								commercial mail delivery service and the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall maintain proof
								of mailing in a form authorized or accepted by the U.S. Postal Service
								or other commercial mail delivery service. No notice is required under
								this subsection if the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> has replaced the insurance. If the
								<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> cancels this policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall credit the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>
								the pro rata unearned portion of the premium. Payment or tender of any
								unearned premium by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall not be a condition precedent to
								the effectiveness of cancellation, but such payment shall be made as
								soon as practicable.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(c)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								If this policy is financed by a premium finance company and is
								canceled, whether by the premium finance company, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>, or the
								<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall return any gross unearned premiums
								that are due under the policy, computed pro rata, to the premium
								finance company for the account of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> within a
								reasonable time not exceeding 45 days after:
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
							<fo:list-block>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(1)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
							<fo:block>
								receipt by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> of a notice of cancellation from the premium finance company or the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>; or
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(2)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
							<fo:block>
								the date the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> cancels the policy.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							</fo:list-block>
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							</fo:list-block>
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block font-weight="bold">
								2.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
							<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
								Nonrenewal
							</fo:block>
							<fo:block>
							<fo:list-block>
							<fo:list-item>
							<fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:block>
								(a)
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-label>
							<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
							<fo:block space-after="4mm">
								This policy may be nonrenewed by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> by mailing to the
								<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, at the address shown in Item 1. of the Declarations,
								written notice of nonrenewal at least 45 days prior to the expiration
								date of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Policy Period</fo:inline>. Such notice shall state the reason for
								nonrenewal. Such notice shall be sent by a first-class mail tracking
								method or by commercial mail delivery service and the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall
								maintain proof of mailing in a form authorized or accepted by the U.S.
								Postal Service or other commercial mail delivery service. No notice is
								required under this subsection if the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> has replaced the
								insurance.
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							</fo:list-block>
							</fo:block>
							</fo:list-item-body>
							</fo:list-item>
							</fo:list-block>
							</fo:block>
						</fo:list-item-body>
					</fo:list-item>
					</fo:list-block>
			</fo:block>
			<fo:block margin-top="4cm"/>
           <fo:block  font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">LPL-AMEND-MD (04/17)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Page 1 of 3</fo:block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block break-after="page" />
		
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">
			
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> provides a renewal policy and notice of premium due
			to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> at least 45 days before the renewal date of the
			policy and the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> fails to make the required payment by the
			renewal date, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may terminate the policy on the renewal date
			for nonpayment of premium after sending to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, by a
			first-class mail tracking method, a written offer to reinstate the
			renewal policy without lapse in coverage. An offer to reinstate shall
			provide not less than 10 days for the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> to make the
			required premium payment.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block>
			(c)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> is being transferred between admitted insurers
			within the same insurance holding company system, the insurer providing
			the new policy shall provide notice of the transfer to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named
			Insured</fo:inline>. The insurer shall be considered to have met the notice
			requirement if the insurer has sent to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> a renewal
			policy that includes a notice of transfer, or a notice on the
			Declarations of the renewal policy, notifying the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Name Insured</fo:inline> that the
			policy has been transferred from the prior named <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> to the new or
			renewing named insurer.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			3.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			Premium Increase
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> seeks to increase the renewal policy premium more
			than 15%, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall send a notice to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> and
			insurance producer, if any, not less than 45 days prior to the renewal
			date of the policy. A notice under this subsection shall include:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			both the expiring policy premium and the renewal policy premium; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			the telephone number for the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> or insurance producer, if any,
			together with a statement that the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> may call to request
			additional information about the premium increase.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> seeks to increase the renewal policy premium and the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer’s</fo:inline> rating methodology requires the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> to provide
			information to calculate the renewal policy premium, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall
			provide a reasonable estimate of the renewal policy premium if the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> has:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			requested the required information from the Named Insured; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			not received the requested information.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
			A reasonable estimate under this subsection shall be based upon the
			information available to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> at the time the notice is sent.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(c)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			The requirements of this subsection do not apply to the extent that the premium increase results from:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			an increase in the units of exposure;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			the application of an experience rating plan; or
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(3)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			a change made by the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insured</fo:inline> that increases the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer’s</fo:inline> exposure.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(d)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			A notice required by this subsection shall be sent by first-class mail and may be sent together with the renewal policy.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(e)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may not be required to comply with any notice
			requirement of this subsection if, not less than 45 days before the
			effective date of the renewal policy, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> has sent:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(i)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, a renewal policy that includes the renewal policy premium; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(ii)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="35mm">
		<fo:block>
			to the insurance producer, if any:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="42mm">
		<fo:block>
			a copy of the renewal policy that includes the renewal policy premium through postal or electronic mail; or
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="42mm">
		<fo:block>
			at the same time as the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> sends the renewal policy to the
			<fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>, a notice of the availability of the renewal policy
			through the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer’s</fo:inline> online electronic system;
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			a written notice of renewal or continuation of coverage that includes the renewal or continuation premium; or
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(3)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			a renewal offer that includes a reasonable estimate of the renewal policy premium.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block start-indent="7mm">
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> fails to comply with any provisions above, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline>
			is liable to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> for the coverage that was requested, or
			that would have become effective except for the failure to comply with
			these provisions, unless the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>: (i) no longer wishes the
			coverage; (ii) has obtained other substantially equivalent coverage; or
			(iii) fails to tender or pay the premium after reasonable demand for
			the premium has been made.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		<fo:block margin-top="2cm"/>
           <fo:block  font-size="9px" color="grey" text-align="left">LPL-AMEND-MD (04/17)&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;
               &#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;&#160;Page 2 of 3</fo:block>
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block break-after="page" />
		
		<fo:block padding-left="5pt"
			font-family="Arial, 'Helvetica Neue', Helvetica, sans-serif;"
			font-size="10px" text-align="justify">
		
		<fo:list-block space-after="8mm">
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label start-indent="7mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold">
			4.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="14mm">
		<fo:block font-weight="bold" space-after="4mm">
			Conditional Renewal
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(a)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			The <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall provide notice to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> if it
			proposes to eliminate or reduce coverage under this policy including a
			reduction in coverage caused by an increase in the Deductible.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(b)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			Such notice shall include a clear and specific description of each change in coverage that identifies:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			the type of coverage that will be changed; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			the dollar amount of the change in coverage.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(c)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			At least 45 days before the change in coverage is scheduled to take
			effect, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> shall send the notice to the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline> by
			first-class mail or “delivery by electronic means”. 
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(d)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block>
			If the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> fails to provide the notice required by this
			subsection, the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Insurer</fo:inline> may not implement the proposed elimination or
			reduction in coverage. 
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(e)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			This subsection does not apply to a change in coverage:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			that is made at the request of the <fo:inline font-weight="bold">Named Insured</fo:inline>; or
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			to a commercial risk that uses the services of a risk manager, broker, or insurance advisor.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item space-after="4mm">
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(f)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="21mm">
		<fo:block space-after="4mm">
			“Delivery by electronic means” includes:
		</fo:block>
		<fo:block>
		<fo:list-block>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(1)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			delivery to an electronic mail address at which a party has consented to receive notice; and
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item>
		<fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:block>
			(2)
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-label>
		<fo:list-item-body start-indent="28mm">
		<fo:block>
			posting on an electronic network, together with separate notice to
			a party directed to the electronic mail address at which the party has
			consented to receive notice of the posting.
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		</fo:block>
		</fo:list-item-body>
		</fo:list-item>
		</fo:list-block>
		<fo:block>
		All other terms, conditions and limitations of the policy remain unaltered.
		</fo:block>
